I think a hate crime that involves murder sends a tremendous message.  Think about if you were a young gay male, afraid to come out, what message hearing the news of Matthew Shepard's death would send to you--he was killed for flirting with someone, beaten to death and hung up on a post like a scarecrow (or J.esus if you prefer the image)... A lot of similarities to Emmitt Till's death to be honest, and there every young African American heard the news about it (apparently this affected Muhammad Ali a lot growing up as a kid).  It sends the message you are isolated for being different and you can be killed for those reasons.  It is an attack aimed at everyone in that category of people.  I think society is right in trying to send a message to counteract the hate crime message, that hate is not tolerated in this society.  This message is positive, it says to the particular targeted group, don't be terrorized by that crime, it's not what society believes in.  <br>
<br>
Of course, South Dakota either doesn't have a hate crime statute or doesn't apply it to gays, so one was not applied there.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A> at: 4/11/02 2:55:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nenjindarkeyes>Nenjin Darkeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 3:05:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4765.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I can agree with that. I'm really only argue the semantics, brought up Injijio I think, that what if that guy that killed that gay boy didnt do it cause he hated gay people, but just because he hated that individual. Granted, the murder at the top of the thread made a statement about lesbians, but what about others? What if you kill a black person because(and am not trying to be racist by this)because he has done drive bys on your friends and killed one. So you kill him, and all of the sudden people tell you that it was a hate crime, and you get an extra 2 life sentences, or even better, get upgraded from a life sentence to a death sentence. <p>Nenjin Darkeyes<BR>
